description:
The Ongoing History of New Music is a Canadian radio program, produced by CFNY in Toronto. The program, hosted by Alan Cross, is also syndicated to several other radio stations across Canada.

The Ongoing History chronicles the history of alternative rock, from its roots in punk and new wave to the modern day. An episode of the show may profile an important musician or band (The Sex Pistols, The Smiths, R.E.M., The Cure, Nirvana, U2, Nine Inch Nails, The Velvet Underground, etc.), a significant musical trend (eg. grunge, Madchester, or a theme such as payola, gay musicians or significant cult figures.
